p: Fits to NHBS ART coverage data gave higher estimates of percentages in care, on ART and virally suppressed (median 2015 estimates: 76%, 69% and 59% respectively), than fits to DH continuum data (median 2015 estimates: 63%, 49% and 41% respectively) (Figure S5f,g,h,i,j,k,l,m). The model predicted 2014 NHBS age/race and ART coverage and 2014 to 2017 DH care validation data well under the corresponding assumptions, but tended to underestimate 2014 to 2017 DH viral suppression (Figure S5a,b,c,d,f,g,h,j,k,l).
